description: Sefa is the Faculty Association for Economics and Business at the University of Amsterdam. With over 4500 members Sefa is one of the leading associations in The Netherlands. More than 60 events are organized every year by 35 committees among which the Sefa Career Month, Room for Discussion and the Amsterdamse Carrière Dagen (Amsterdam Career Days). The daily management of the association and supervision of the committees lies with the board with a workload of 60 hours a week. As Project Officer within the Sefa board, I am responsible for the supervising of all the large career events that are organized by Sefa, namely Accountancy Tour, Amsterdam Marketing Challenge, Amsterdamse Carriere Dagen (Amsterdam Career Days), Consultancy Event, International Career Event, Masters of Finance, The top of Tax, Sefa Career Month and the Sefa Conference. Besides this, I develop a vision on the long term goals of the projects. An overview of my tasks as Project Officer: • Responsible for Sefa’s largest career projects and it's long term strategy • Guiding committees in the fields of planning and acquisition • Setting out commercial policy together with the Commercial Officer • Recruiting suitable career committee members

description: Sefa is the Faculty Association for Economics and Business at the University of Amsterdam. With over 6.500 members Sefa is one of the leading associations in The Netherlands. More than 60 events are organised every year by 35 committees among which Room for Discussion, Amsterdamse Carrière Dagen and the Sefa Conference. The daily management of the association and supervision of the committees lies with the board with a fulltime workload. As the Commercial Officer I am responsible for: • Communication with commercial relations • Generating Sefa’s cash flow • Exploring the market and making new contacts • Commercial strategy both short and long term • Supervisor Amsterdamse Carrière Dagen and Commercial Team

description: The Amsterdamse Carrière Dagen (ACD) is the largest career event of its kind in Amsterdam, with more then 60 companies and 1600 students. The ACD is a cooperation between the University of Amsterdam and VU University. The aim of the ACD is to guide students in the choices at the beginning of their careers. Leading multinational companies from different sectors, nonprofit organizations, organizations from the public sector and other companies will be participating. Together with four fellow committee-members, I am responsible for the acquisition of the participating companies.

description: Customer Support-Assisted all DHS customer in all areas of support. Provided quotes, and technical support mostly. A colleague and I receive all of the after hours support calls from the company hotline. Sales Support-Assisted all DHS Business Development Representatives with sales, technical support, and customer support. Also worked directly with all prime vendors under the TLS contract. I was their direct point of contact, and I provided them with any support needed. It was my job to search through bid sites for open solicitations, and assist all customer's working under direct contracts. Distribution Support-I am the point of contact for all of our current distributors, as well as the main point of contact for anything done with Reeves EMS (DHS's medical brand of equipment). Assisted the Distributor's in all areas of support, including technical support, providing quotes, and review and submitting Purchase Orders submitted by the Distributors. CRM Support-I work with executive rights to our company's CRM database. I am responsible for the majority of all sales entry and updates. This includes assisting other employees with any issues they may come across within the CRM database. I am responsible for setting up new customers in the system, as well as many other duties and responsibilities within the CRM.
